<p class="indent2" style="-uslm-lc:I13" xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:dcterms="http://purl.org/dc/terms/" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">A member of a uniformed service (within the meaning of <ref href="/us/usc/t37/s101/3">section 101(3) of title 37</ref> of the United States Code) is in a missing status for any period for which he is entitled to pay and allowances under section 552 of such title 37.</p>
